<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1923-03-20T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1923-03-20T06:00:00-05:00" n="219" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d219">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">868.48/375: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Greece</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Athens</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-03-20T13:00:00+02:00"><hi rend="italic">March 20,
                                        1923—1 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 1:30
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>56. Haskell left Greece March 19 for Anatolia on an American destroyer to
                            take up with Turkish authorities a proposal of Mr. Hoover<note n="7" xml:id="d219fn7">Chairman of the American Relief
                                Administration.</note> relating to American relief for Turkish
                            devastated regions on condition that the Turks permit refugees in Greece
                            to return to their homes in Turkey. This matter is being kept
                            confidential in Athens and is not known to the Greek authorities.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Caffery</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>